South African Reserve Bank's Governor Says Inflation Upside Risk Increases

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-03-15T07:10:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/south-africa-reserve-bank-s-marcus-says-inflation-upside-risk-increases.html
  South Africa  Reserve Bank’s
Professor  Gill Marcus  said the nation is facing rising threats
to inflation and upside risk has increased, during a speech in
Johannesburg today.  Marcus also said South Africa’s debt to GDP ratio may
“peak” at 43 percent and that the country’s GDP is not
sufficient for  job creation .  Marcus also said there are questions to be asked about the
safety of nuclear energy in the wake of  Japan ’s ongoing post-
earthquake crisis.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Agnes Nikoi at 
 anikoi@bloomberg.net  